pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132581582,imgsize-301634.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[FDA recalls 1.6 million dozen eggs over Salmonella risk across five US states]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132580310.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/nearly-1-6-million-dozen-eggs-recalled-over-possible-salmonella-contamination-after-fda-alert-with-kroger-and-brookshire-stores-in-five-us-states-affected/articleshow/132580310.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/nearly-1-6-million-dozen-eggs-recalled-over-possible-salmonella-contamination-after-fda-alert-with-kroger-and-brookshire-stores-in-five-us-states-affected/articleshow/132580310.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-23T17:42:23+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132580505,imgsize-734726.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Remains of Grand Canyon trekker found after 15 years]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132580157.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In December 2025, human remains were identified as those of William Ott, a skilled hiker who vanished during his quest for ancient rock art in the Grand Canyon back in April 2012. The search for Ott concluded after his daypack was discovered nearby, containing personal items. Authorities used DNA testing to confirm his identity after years of searching for answers.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/remains-of-grand-canyon-hiker-found-after-nearly-15-year-search/articleshow/132580157.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/remains-of-grand-canyon-hiker-found-after-nearly-15-year-search/articleshow/132580157.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-23T17:41:16+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132580461,imgsize-297736.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Thousands of idle ships trapped near the Strait of Hormuz could become floating nurseries for invasive marine species]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132576193.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Ships lingering in the Persian Gulf could unintentionally facilitate the spread of harmful marine invaders worldwide. Extended anchorage allows marine organisms to thrive on the hulls, creating significant biofouling concerns that threaten global maritime commerce. These invasive species can inflict extensive ecological and economic harm on coastal areas. It is imperative for nations to join forces to address biofouling issues and prevent future outbreaks of invasion.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/thousands-of-idle-ships-trapped-near-the-strait-of-hormuz-could-become-floating-nurseries-for-invasive-marine-species-and-spread-them-worldwide-when-trade-resumes/articleshow/132576193.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/thousands-of-idle-ships-trapped-near-the-strait-of-hormuz-could-become-floating-nurseries-for-invasive-marine-species-and-spread-them-worldwide-when-trade-resumes/articleshow/132576193.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-23T14:55:47+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132576285,imgsize-89828.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Nike employees divert $2 million in Nike shoes from a Memphis warehouse in a cargo theft scheme]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132575937.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Federal prosecutors in the US have charged 12 people in an alleged scheme that diverted at least $2 million worth of Nike shoes from the company's Memphis logistics centre. According to the indictment, unauthorised UPS shipping labels were used to redirect thousands of cartons to resellers across the country. The defendants deny no charges yet, and the allegations will be tested in court.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/ups-labels-were-allegedly-used-to-divert-at-least-2-million-in-nike-shoes-from-a-memphis-warehouse-in-a-cargo-theft-scheme-involving-former-nike-employees-and-sneaker-resellers/articleshow/132575937.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/ups-labels-were-allegedly-used-to-divert-at-least-2-million-in-nike-shoes-from-a-memphis-warehouse-in-a-cargo-theft-scheme-involving-former-nike-employees-and-sneaker-resellers/articleshow/132575937.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-23T17:45:06+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132576591,imgsize-86762.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[California to spend $36.4 mn repairing historic Ebbetts Pass where highway climbs 8000 feet]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132577045.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Caltrans will begin a $36.4 million project on August 3 to repair 31.7 miles of California's Highway 4, including the historic Ebbetts Pass in the Sierra Nevada. The four-year project will improve road surfaces, drainage and safety features while causing temporary lane closures and occasional full highway closures until 2030.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/california-will-spend-36-4-million-repairing-ebbetts-pass-one-of-the-last-wild-trans-sierra-routes-where-the-highway-climbs-above-8000-feet-and-narrows-to-one-lane/articleshow/132577045.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/california-will-spend-36-4-million-repairing-ebbetts-pass-one-of-the-last-wild-trans-sierra-routes-where-the-highway-climbs-above-8000-feet-and-narrows-to-one-lane/articleshow/132577045.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-23T17:30:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132579474,imgsize-194758.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Florida scientists bring endangered elkhorn coral ashore fearing another heatwave could drive it to extinction]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132579004.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/florida-scientists-bring-endangered-elkhorn-coral-ashore-fearing-another-heatwave-could-drive-it-to-extinction/articleshow/132579004.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/florida-scientists-bring-endangered-elkhorn-coral-ashore-fearing-another-heatwave-could-drive-it-to-extinction/articleshow/132579004.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-23T16:58:09+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132579213,imgsize-1161566.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Indian-origin couple convicted in UK over Covid PPE fraud that funded £126k Porsche, Rolexes]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132576574.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/indian-origin-couple-convicted-in-uk-over-covid-ppe-fraud-that-funded-126k-porsche-rolexes/articleshow/132576574.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/indian-origin-couple-convicted-in-uk-over-covid-ppe-fraud-that-funded-126k-porsche-rolexes/articleshow/132576574.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-23T16:05:10+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132577985,imgsize-682210.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Australian agronomist Tony Rinaudo's FMNR revives Niger's dry landscapes with 200 million trees]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132576961.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[An Australian agronomist's simple idea transformed Niger's dry landscapes into a success story. Tony Rinaudo helped farmers regenerate over 200 million trees by reviving existing root systems. This low-cost approach restored millions of hectares of degraded farmland and improved food security. Indigenous trees regenerated, providing shade, preventing soil erosion, and enriching the soil. The technique is now a global model for restoring degraded land worldwide.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/an-australian-forest-maker-helped-farmers-in-niger-regrow-more-than-200-million-trees-by-pruning-living-stumps-roots-and-seeds-hidden-beneath-dry-land/articleshow/132576961.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/an-australian-forest-maker-helped-farmers-in-niger-regrow-more-than-200-million-trees-by-pruning-living-stumps-roots-and-seeds-hidden-beneath-dry-land/articleshow/132576961.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-23T15:35:06+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132577037,imgsize-105974.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by Charles Darwin: "Ignorance more frequently begets confidence..."]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132559227.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/quote-of-the-day-by-charles-darwin-ignorance-more-frequently-begets-confidence-than-does-knowledge-it-is-those-who/articleshow/132559227.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/quote-of-the-day-by-charles-darwin-ignorance-more-frequently-begets-confidence-than-does-knowledge-it-is-those-who/articleshow/132559227.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-22T18:20:21+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132567094,imgsize-280726.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meet Evan Budz: The 16-year-old Canadian who built an AI-powered robot turtle to detect microplastics with 94% accuracy]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132576962.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/meet-evan-budz-the-16-year-old-canadian-who-built-an-ai-powered-robot-turtle-to-detect-microplastics-with-94-accuracy/articleshow/132576962.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/meet-evan-budz-the-16-year-old-canadian-who-built-an-ai-powered-robot-turtle-to-detect-microplastics-with-94-accuracy/articleshow/132576962.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-23T15:40:26+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132577125,imgsize-1185129.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists revisit a forgotten Soviet plan to dam the Bering Strait and see if it could help protect Earth's climate]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132576125.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Soviet engineer Petr Borisov proposed damming the Bering Strait to warm Siberia.  This bold plan aimed to transform frozen lands into productive agricultural areas.  Modern researchers now study closing the strait to stabilize ocean circulation.  Their simulations explore impacts on the Atlantic Meridional Overturning Circulation system.  Scientists remain cautious about such large-scale environmental interventions.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/scientists-revisit-a-forgotten-soviet-plan-to-dam-the-bering-strait-and-see-if-it-could-help-protect-earths-climate/articleshow/132576125.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/scientists-revisit-a-forgotten-soviet-plan-to-dam-the-bering-strait-and-see-if-it-could-help-protect-earths-climate/articleshow/132576125.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-23T14:00:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132576178,imgsize-167204.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Orcas filmed tearing apart giant Sunfish with new hunting technique]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132574246.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Researchers have documented a previously unknown hunting behaviour in orcas in the Gulf of California. The animals were filmed working together to hold and ram giant sharp-tail sunfish until the carcass broke into thousands of pieces. Scientists believe the behaviour may help younger orcas feed more easily or could simply be play.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/orcas-in-the-gulf-of-california-were-filmed-using-a-coordinated-ramming-technique-that-made-a-giant-sunfish-break-into-thousands-of-pieces-possibly-to-help-a-juvenile-feed/articleshow/132574246.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/orcas-in-the-gulf-of-california-were-filmed-using-a-coordinated-ramming-technique-that-made-a-giant-sunfish-break-into-thousands-of-pieces-possibly-to-help-a-juvenile-feed/articleshow/132574246.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-23T13:40:14+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132574744,imgsize-37604.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Tony Parker's mansion slashes price: Texas estate drops to $11 million; despite luxury features, still seeking buyer]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132575392.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Tony Parker's Texas mansion has seen another significant price reduction. The sprawling estate is now listed for eleven million dollars after several adjustments. This luxurious property features an enormous private water park and extensive sports facilities. Despite extensive publicity and a past peak price of twenty million dollars, it remains unsold. The highly customized luxury estate continues its search for a new owner.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/real-estate/news/tony-parkers-53-acre-texas-estate-once-asked-20-million-but-the-former-spurs-stars-mansion-with-a-private-water-park-is-now-listed-for-11-million/articleshow/132575392.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/real-estate/news/tony-parkers-53-acre-texas-estate-once-asked-20-million-but-the-former-spurs-stars-mansion-with-a-private-water-park-is-now-listed-for-11-million/articleshow/132575392.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-23T13:50:47+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Real Estate Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132575379,imgsize-130828.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Margot Robbie secretly splashes $28m on a Queensland ranch estate]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132574988.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Margot Robbie has made headlines with her recent acquisition of a lavish estate in Queensland, costing $28 million. Nestled in the scenic Currumbin Valley, this property holds significant nostalgia for the actress, as it's near where she grew up. After leaving the Gold Coast in her youth to chase her acting ambitions, this return represents a heartfelt reconnection with her origins during her flourishing career.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/real-estate/margot-robbie-secretly-splashes-28m-on-a-queensland-ranch-estate-with-horse-stables-pool-tennis-court-and-10-car-garage/articleshow/132574988.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/real-estate/margot-robbie-secretly-splashes-28m-on-a-queensland-ranch-estate-with-horse-stables-pool-tennis-court-and-10-car-garage/articleshow/132574988.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-23T13:24:43+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Real Estate Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132575012,imgsize-1836